dcterms:description: The training set consists of 199 clinical notes, which were collected from four types of clinical notes including discharge summaries (DIS), radiology reports (RAD), and ECG/ECHO reports. Disorder entities were annotated for each note and then mapped to concepts. The training set contained 5811 disorder entities which were mapped to 1007 unique CUIs or CUI-less.
dcterms:title: Training Set

dcterms:description: The development set contains 99 clinical notes, which were collected from the same sources as the training set. It includes 5340 disorder entities mapped to 795 CUIs or CUI-less.
dcterms:title: Development Set

dcterms:description: The test set consists of 133 clinical notes, all of which are discharge summaries. The gold-standard annotation of the test set is not released by the organizer.
dcterms:title: Test Set
